      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/54/9",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ أَ يُحْرِمُ اَلرَّجُلُ فِي اَلثَّوْبِ اَلْأَسْوَدِ قَالَ «لاَ يُحْرِمُ فِي اَلثَّوْبِ اَلْأَسْوَدِ وَ لاَ يُكَفَّنُ فِيهِ اَلْمَيِّتُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2602 - It was narrated from Al-Husayn ibn al-Mukhtar, who said:\nI said to Abu Abdullah (as): \"Can a man enter Ihram wearing a black garment?\"\nImam (as) said: \"He should not enter Ihram in a black garment, nor should a deceased person be shrouded in it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
